==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enterotomy
<hw>En`ter*ot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'e`nteron</grk> an intestine + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Incision of the intestines, especially in
reducing certain cases of hernia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

